data_adit_interface_dictionary

save__Entry_interview.Sf_category

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Sf_category'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Category definition for the information content of the saveframe
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Sf category
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
entry_interview
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.Sf_framecode

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Sf_framecode'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
A code that uniquely identifies the saveframe within the entry.  The code can be a human readable identifier that defines the contents of the saveframe (see the examples).
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Sf framecode
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
entry_interview
;

   stop_

save_

   _Description

     _Example

save_

save__Entry_interview.Sf_ID

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Sf_ID'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
An integer value that is the unique identifier for the saveframe that applies across the archive.  This value is not stable and may be reassigned each time the data are loaded into a database system.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Sf ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
34
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.ID

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.ID'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
An integer value that uniquely identifies the entry interview saveframe for this entry from all other entry interview saveframes present in the entry.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
1
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.PDB_deposition

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.PDB_deposition'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Check this box, if you are depositing atomic coordinates to be archived at the Protein Data Bank.  With this box checked, after clicking on the 'Save Changes' button, you will be asked to enter additional information regarding the data submitted. Files containing the data sets should be uploaded by filling out the form found by clicking on the 'Deposit data files' link in the frame on the left of the screen.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
PDB deposition
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.View_mode

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.View_mode'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
The 'view mode' buttons are used to select between a view of the PDB/BMRB or the BMRB only deposition requirements. The majority of the information you enter will apply to both depositions. When in the PDB/BMRB view mode, a deposition when submitted will go to both PDB and BMRB.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
</td><td colspan='99'></td></tr><tr style='height:6em; vertical-align:middle;'><td class=category_cell_mandatory_label>Start a PDB/BMRB deposition or a BMRB only deposition
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
PDB
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.Use_previous_BMRB_entry

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Use_previous_BMRB_entry'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Indicate yes or no whether the deposition has used chemcial shift data taken from an existing BMRB entry.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Is this deposition based on chemical shift data taken from an existing BMRB entry?
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
no
;

   stop_

save__Entry_interview.Non_standard_residues

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Non_standard_residues'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Check this box if any of the biopolymers in the molecular system studied contained non-standard amino acid residues or nucleotides. This includes chemically modified residues such as phosphorylated amino acids.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
At least one biopolymer contains a non-standard residue
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
no
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.Constraints

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Constraints'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Check this box, if you are depositing constraints used to calculate a three-dimensional structure for the molecular assembly.  With this box checked, after clicking on the 'Save Changes' button, you will be asked to enter additional information regarding the data submitted. Files containing the data sets should be uploaded by filling out the form found by clicking on the 'Deposit data files' link in the frame on the left of the screen.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name

Structural constraints (restraint data)
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry_interview.Assigned_chem_shifts

   _Tag                  '_Entry_interview.Assigned_chem_shifts'

   _Category              'Entry_interview'

   _Description
;
Check this box, if you are depositing one or more sets of assigned chemical shifts for the reported molecular assembly.  If you have just started a deposition, after clicking on the 'Save Changes' button, you will be asked to upload the appropriate data files and later enter additional information regarding the data submitted. At anytime during a deposition session, data containing files can be uploaded by filling out the form found by clicking on 'Entry information' and then the 'Deposit data files' link in the frame on the left of the screen.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Assigned NMR chemical shifts
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes
;

   stop_

   _Tag                  '_Deposited_data_files.Precheck_flag'

   _Category              'Deposited_data_files'

   _Description
;
Precheck confirms that the data files you enter are in a format that can be automatically processed by our software. The format and required data items for coordinate files are described for the PDB and mmCIF formats. The precheck identifies any changes that need to be made in your data files in order to obtain a validation report or to deposit your structure.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Precheck
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes
;

   stop_

save__Deposited_data_files.Validate_flag

   _Tag                  '_Deposited_data_files.Validate_flag'

   _Category              'Deposited_data_files'

   _Description
;
The validation check creates a validation report for the structure which includes an RCSB Atlas page, a validation report with stereochemical checks, and, depending on the type and content of the files uploaded, produces Procheck and NUCheck reports. The validation may take a few minutes depending on the size of your structure, so please be patient.
;

Validate

save_

save__Study.Name

   _Tag                  '_Study.Name'

   _Category              'Study'

   _Description
;
If this deposition combined with past entries or entries planned for the future will constitute a 'study' of a biopolymer, a name for the study can be entered in this field.  The name should be brief but descriptive similar to the title of a paper or review article. A study is a collection of entries containing data for a set of related molecular systems (a series of single amino acid or nucleic acid variants) or for a single molecular system but published in more than one citation (i.e., chemical shifts in one publication, atomic coordinates in another, and an investigation of the polymer in complex with another polymer in a third). In rare cases, an entry may be a member of more than one study.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Study name
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
Investigation of cytochrome b in the molten globule state
;

   stop_

save_

   _Tag                  '_Study.Type'

Study type

   loop_
     _Example

;
structure study

save__Entry.Dep_release_code_nmr_constraints

   _Tag                  '_Entry.Dep_release_code_nmr_constraints'

   _Category              'Entry'

   _Description
;
Select the status or terms to be applied for the release of the NMR constraint data to the public. Depositors are encourage to make their data available to the public as quickly as possible.  However, requests may be made to hold the data for a limited period of time up to one year.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Release status for constraints
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
RELEASE NOW
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entry.Dep_release_code_sequence

   _Tag                  '_Entry.Dep_release_code_sequence'

   _Category              'Entry'

   _Description
;
Select the status or terms to be applied for the prerelease of the sequence information for the biopolymers to the public. Although the atomic coordinate and other data may be placed 'on hold', immediate release of the polymer sequence data will allow others, including the structural genomics centers, to identify polymers that have been studied and to select other targets reducing duplicate effort.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Prerelease status for polymer sequences
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
RELEASE NOW
;

   stop_

An integer value that is the unique identifier for the saveframe that applies across the archive.  This value is not stable and may be reassigned each time the data are loaded into a database system.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Sf ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save_

save__Citation.Journal_abbrev

   _Tag                  '_Citation.Journal_abbrev'

   _Category              'Citation'

   _Description
;
Enter a standard journal abbreviation as defined by the Chemical Abstract Services for the journal where the data are or will be published. A pull down list of common journals is provided. If the data in the deposition are related to a J. Biomol. NMR paper, the value must be 'J. Biomol. NMR' to alert the BMRB annotators so that the deposition is properly processed.  If the depositor truly does not know the journal, a value of 'not known' or 'na' is acceptable.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Journal abbreviation
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
J. Biomol. NMR
;

   stop_

   _Category              'Entity_assembly'

   _Description
;
For biopolymers or ligands, does the indicated component of the system represent an observed conformational isomer of another component of the system.  For example, component one may represent a polypeptide chain with proline 34 in the cis conformation and component two may represent the polypeptide chain with proline 34 in the trans conformation. In another example, component one may be alpha-D-glucose and component two beta-D-glucose.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
NMR observable conformational isomer
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes
;

   stop_

   _Tag                  '_Entity_assembly.Magnetic_equivalence_group_code'

   _Category              'Entity_assembly'

   _Description
;
Unique identifier for the group of assembly components within the assembly that are magnetically equivalent in that only one set of NMR peaks are observed for the group. For example, this is the usual situation for a protein homodimer. Thus one enters the same number in the boxes for component #1 and comonent #2, if these represent the two proteins making up the homodimer.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Magnetic equivalence group code
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
1
;

   stop_

save__Deleted_atom.Entity_assembly_name

   _Tag                  '_Deleted_atom.Entity_assembly_name'

   _Category              'Deleted_atom'

   _Description
;
Provide the name given to the molecule in the molecular assembly where the deleted atom is located.  There may be several identical biopolymers in the system, but the one where the specific atom has been deleted needs to be specified.  If the same atom is missing from multiple polymers in the system, a row in this table needs to be created for each deleted atom.  In this way a complete and accurate chemical structure for the molecular system can be constructed.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Deleted atom molecular assembly component name
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save_

save__Assembly_subsystem.Molecular_mass

   _Tag                  '_Assembly_subsystem.Molecular_mass'

   _Category              'Assembly_subsystem'

   _Description
;
The approximate mass of the system as defined by the authors and is intended to approximate the sum of the masses of all of the atoms in the system.  No attempt  is made to define the mass at a specific pH value, in terms of the protonation  state of any pH titratable groups, or according to the incorporation of isotopes.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Molecular mass
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
24000
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entity.Sf_framecode

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Sf_framecode'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;
Enter a brief name for the molecule.  Please do NOT include organism names or descriptions for the function of the molecule.  The name defines a unique chemical entity (a biopolymer or organic or inorganic ligand including metal ions).  There may be many instances of the entity in the molecular system.  For a homodimer, the biopolymer is described only once in this section of the deposition, but is listed twice in the section above for the molecular system and each instance is given a different name.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Brief molecule name or acronym (label)
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
HIV protease polypeptide
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entity.Entry_ID

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Entry_ID'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;

save__Entity.Polymer_strand_ID

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Polymer_strand_ID'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;
Please enter the chain identifier assigned to this molecular entity in the deposited atomic coordinate file. For a single polymer in the deposited coordinates, the chain identifier may be assigned the value 'A'.<br>For a homodimer in the deposited coordinate set, the chain identifiers maybe 'A' and 'B'. For a heterodimer, one entity may have a chain ID of 'A' and the other 'B'. More complex system like those with multiple bound metal ions may have a large number of chain identifiers.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Chain identifiers
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
A
;

   stop_

save__Entity.Polymer_seq_one_letter_code

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Polymer_seq_one_letter_code'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;
Provide the complete sequence of a protein or nucleic acid as it existed in the NMR tube expressed using the one-letter code for standard residues and an X for non-standard residues. Include residues for cloning tags, etc. and for all residues even when experimental data are not reported.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Enter the complete polymer sequence (one-letter code) <BR><BR>Include all cloning artifacts, his tags, and disordered residues.<BR>The sequence must represent the complete polymer<BR> as found in the NMR tube.
;

   loop_
     _Example

HHHHHHAFGCRESWQAKCLPHNMVIXSDF
;

save_

save__Entity.Ambiguous_conformational_states

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Ambiguous_conformational_states'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;
Please indicate by answering yes or no if the molecule exists in multiple conformational states that have not been or cannot be clearly defined.  In some cases, proteins have been found to exhibit multiple peaks for a single proton or carbon atom that may be caused by cis/trans isomerization at one or more proline residue. If the peaks have not been associated specifically with the isomeric state of a defined proline residue, the conformational heterogeneity of the protein has not been determined and the molecule exists in undetermined or ambiguous conformational states.  Similar circumstances may exist for other kinds of biopolymers and ligands.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Ambiguous conformational states are present
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
no
;

   stop_

save_

save__Entity.Ambiguous_chem_comp_sites

   _Tag                  '_Entity.Ambiguous_chem_comp_sites'

   _Category              'Entity'

   _Description
;
At times, biopolymers purified from natural sources are found to be a mixture of homologs that differ at one residue position (ser or thr at position 12).  It may either be very difficult to separate the homologs or the residue ambiguity may not be discovered until well into a study. If such sequence residue ambiguity exists in the reported polymer, please indicate this by answering the question 'yes'.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Ambiguous residue sites exist
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
no
;

   stop_

Please enter the PubChem Substance ID for the chemical compound.  If a PubChem substance ID is found and entered for the component, BMRB will be able to complete the remaining mandatory fields required to describe the chemical compound.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
PubChem Substance ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
33768
;

   stop_

save__Sample.Aggregate_sample_number

   _Tag                  '_Sample.Aggregate_sample_number'

   _Category              'Sample'

   _Description
;
Enter the total number of samples represented by the concentration value (range) reported. Often more than one 15N or 13C;15N labeled sample is required to collect all of the data required to assign the spectra of a protein or nucleic acid. If this is the case for the study reported in this deposition, the total number of samples used matching the contents and concentrations supplied can be entered in this field.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Aggregate sample number
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
3
;

   stop_

save__Sample_component.Mol_common_name

   _Tag                  '_Sample_component.Mol_common_name'

   _Category              'Sample_component'

   _Description
;
Enter the common name for the component of the sample, include the molecules in the study (biopolymers and ligands) as well as buffers, salts, reducing agents, anti-bacterial agents, etc. Common buffers, salts, and other compounds can be selected from the pull down list.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Molecule common name
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
CheY; DTT; PMSF
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_component.Isotopic_labeling

   _Tag                  '_Sample_component.Isotopic_labeling'

   _Category              'Sample_component'

   _Description
;
If the molecule was isotopically labeled, provide a description of the labeling using the format recommended by the IUPAC/IUBMB/IUPAB Interunion Task Group. Commonly used labeling patterns are provide in the pull down list in the IUPAC format.  If a different labeling pattern was used, please enter the correct value using the examples in the pull down list as a guide to the proper format.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Isotopic labeling
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
[U-95% 13C; U-90% 15N]
;

   stop_

save__Sample_component.Concentration_val

   _Tag                  '_Sample_component.Concentration_val'

   _Category              'Sample_component'

   _Description
;
Enter a value for the concentration of the sample component (units will be entered below). This may be either a single value (prefered, if available), but may also be a range (0.9-1.2), if appropriate.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Concentration value (or range)
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
2 or 0.7-1.2
;

   stop_

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_list.ID'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_list'

   _Description
;
A value that uniquely identifies the set of sample conditions from other sample
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_condition_list.Details

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_list.Details'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_list'

   _Description
;
General details describing conditions of both the sample and the environment during the measurements can be entered in this field.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Details
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
The high salinity of the sample may have contributed to overheating of the sample during experiments with long saturation periods like the TOCSY experiments.
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_condition_variable.Type

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_variable.Type'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_variable'

   _Description
;
The name of the variable used to define a specific sample condition (i.e., temperature) when conducting experiments used to derive the experimental data included in the file.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Variable type
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
temperature, pressure, pH
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_condition_variable.Val

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_variable.Val'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_variable'

   _Description
;
Value for the variable (temperature, pressure, pH) defined in the previous field.  Do not include the units in this field. The units for the value are entered in a following field.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Variable value
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
308
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_condition_variable.Val_err

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_variable.Val_err'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_variable'

   _Description
;
Provide the estimated error on the value for the sample condition given in the previous field.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Variable value error
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
0.2
;

   stop_

save_

save__Sample_condition_variable.Val_units

   _Tag                  '_Sample_condition_variable.Val_units'

   _Category              'Sample_condition_variable'

   _Description
;
Provide the units for the value of the sample condition (temperature, pressure, pH, ect.) given in the previous field.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Variable value units
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
K
;

   stop_

save_

save__Experiment.Sample_label

   _Tag                  '_Experiment.Sample_label'

   _Category              'Experiment'

   _Description
;
Enter the label assigned to one sample listed above in the section where samples and their contents were entered. A pull down list of sample labels should appear, if the samples have been defined above. If the same NMR experiment was carried out with more than one sample, enter a new row in the table for each time the NMR experiment was carried out. For example, if a 1H-15N HSQC experiment was run on an 15N labeled sample and a 15N-13C labeled sample, two rows should be entered one with the 15N sample indicated and one with the 15N-13C sample indicated.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Sample label
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
sample_1
;

   stop_

After clicking on the 'Save Changes' button, the fields for the 1H chemical shift referencing will be automatically filled in with the appropriate values.
;

save_

save__Chem_shift_ref.Indirect_shift_ratio

   _Tag                  '_Chem_shift_ref.Indirect_shift_ratio'

   _Category              'Chem_shift_ref'

   _Description
;
The Chi value used in calculating the chemical shift referencing values for nuclei that are referenced indirectly.  The values used should be those recommended by the IUPAC Taskforce on the deposition of data to the public databases [Markley, et al.  Pure and Appl. Chem. 70, 117-142 (1998)]. Usually the value entered for 1H chemical shift referencing would be 1.0.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Indirect chemical shift ratio
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save_

save__Chem_shift_ref.External_ref_loc

   _Tag                  '_Chem_shift_ref.External_ref_loc'

   _Category              'Chem_shift_ref'

   _Description
;
External chemical shift references are defined as compounds used to reference chemical shifts that are kept physically separated from the molecules being studied. The reference compound may be placed either within the same NMR sample tube as the experimental sample commonly using a cylindrical or spherical insert that contains the reference compound or in a completely separate NMR sample tube. In the latter case, an insert also may be used, but the reference compound sample and the experimental sample are not in the NMR spectrometer at the same time. When a coaxial insert is used for the reference sample, the reference sample may either be located at the outer edge of the NMR tube or at the center. Please select the item that best describes the method you have used.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
External reference compound location
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
insert at center of experimental sample tube
;

   stop_

save_

   _Tag                  '_Chem_shift_ref.External_ref_sample_geometry'

   _Category              'Chem_shift_ref'

   _Description
;
The geometrical shape of the external reference sample. The reference sample may be either in a capillary inserted into the tube containing the experimental sample or in a completely separate NMR tube.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
External reference sample geometry
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
spherical; cylindrical; etc.
;

   stop_

save__Ambiguous_atom_chem_shift.Ambiguous_shift_set_ID

   _Tag                  '_Ambiguous_atom_chem_shift.Ambiguous_shift_set_ID'

   _Category              'Ambiguous_atom_chem_shift'

   _Description
;
An integer value that defines a set of chemical shifts that form a mutually ambiguous group. For ambiguity codes of 4 or 5, various combinations of assigned chemical shifts may form sets where the chemical shift assignments are not specifically known, but it is known that the chemical shifts belong to one atom in the set.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Shift set ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

   _Category              'H_exch_protection_factor'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth seq ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;

   _Category              'Dipole_dipole_relax'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth seq ID 1
;

     _Example

   _Category              'Cross_correlation_DD_list'

   _Description
;
Please enter the units for the cross correlation dipole-dipole relaxation values reported.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;

;

   loop_
     _Example

;
s-1
;

   stop_

save__Deduced_secd_struct_exptl.Auth_seq_ID_start

   _Tag                  '_Deduced_secd_struct_exptl.Auth_seq_ID_start'

   _Category              'Deduced_secd_struct_exptl'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth seq ID start
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   _Tag                  '_Conformer_stat_list.Conformer_ensemble_only'

   _Category              'Conformer_stat_list'

   _Description
;
Check this box if your atomic coordinate file contains data for an ensemble of structures, where one structure from the ensemble will be designated as a representative structure. All of the members of the ensemble have been calculated using the same method.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Are you depositing coordinates only <br>for an ensemble of conformers
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save_

save__Conformer_stat_list.Both_ensemble_and_rep_conformer

   _Tag                  '_Conformer_stat_list.Both_ensemble_and_rep_conformer'

   _Category              'Conformer_stat_list'

   _Description
;
Select this box if your atomic coordinate file contains data for an ensemble of conformers and a representative conformer derived using a method different from that used for the other conformers in the file.  An example would be a file that contains an ensemble of conformers calculated from the NMR constraints and one conformer that was derived as an averaged minimized structure from the other conformers in the file.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Are you depositing coordinates for both an ensemble of conformers <br>and an independently derived representative conformer derived from the ensemble
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
;

   stop_

save__Constraint_stat_list_ens.Constraint_stats_not_available

   _Tag                  '_Constraint_stat_list_ens.Constraint_stats_not_available'

   _Category              'Constraint_stat_list_ens'

   _Description
;
Depositors are strongly encouraged to provide a few statistics related to the constraints used to calculate the ensemble of conformers and the conformer ensemble. If the statistics are not available, the box provided can be checked and the constraint statistics page saved. This will remove the mandatory requirement to enter the statistical data.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Constraint statistics for an ensemble of conformers are not available
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
yes/no
;

   stop_

   _Tag                  '_Bond_annotation.Auth_seq_ID_1'

   _Category              'Bond_annotation'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name

   _Category              'Gen_dist_constraint'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.

save__Floating_chirality.Auth_seq_ID_1

   _Tag                  '_Floating_chirality.Auth_seq_ID_1'

   _Category              'Floating_chirality'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth seq ID 1
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
-3
;

   stop_

save__CA_CB_constraint.Auth_seq_ID_1

   _Tag                  '_CA_CB_constraint.Auth_seq_ID_1'

   _Category              'CA_CB_constraint'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Seq_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Seq_ID or Comp_index_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth seq ID 1
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
-3
;

   stop_

save__H_chem_shift_constraint.Auth_asym_ID

   _Tag                  '_H_chem_shift_constraint.Auth_asym_ID'

   _Category              'H_chem_shift_constraint'

   _Description
;
An alternative identifier for Asym_id that may be provided by an author in order to match that used in the publication that describes the experimental data.  Note that the value is not required to be a number and does not need to correspond to the value for Asym_ID or Entity_assembly_ID.
;

   _Adit_item_view_name
;
Auth asym ID
;

   loop_
     _Example

;
?
